# EVELYN — .gitignore
# Public repo: never commit raw phishing/WHOIS/security data, saved
# graph objects, or anything containing live infrastructure details
# scraped during research. Figures (PNG/JPG/PDF) ARE committed —
# they're the evidence/output, not the raw data.

# ── Raw and processed research data ──────────────────────
# PhishTank/Tranco CSVs, WHOIS dumps, cert cache, checkpoints —
# never published, since this is scraped third-party + live
# infrastructure data, not original content.
data/raw/*
data/processed/*
!data/raw/.gitkeep
!data/processed/.gitkeep

# ── Saved graph objects ───────────────────────────────────
# .pkl files are serialized NetworkX graphs containing real domain
# names, IPs, WHOIS records, and other live infrastructure detail
# pulled during investigation. These never go into a public repo —
# only the FIGURES generated from them (which present the findings,
# not the raw scraped data) are committed.
data/graphs/*.pkl
data/graphs/*.gpickle
!data/graphs/.gitkeep

# ── Certificate transparency cache ────────────────────────
data/processed/cert_cache/

# ── Python ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.env
venv/
.venv/

# ── Editors ────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/

# ── Jupyter ────────────────────────────────────────────────
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ── Results — figures ARE committed (this is the published evidence) ──
# Only exclude scratch/demo figures and oversized raw metric dumps.
results/figures/_demo_*
results/metrics/*.csv
!results/metrics/.gitkeep

# ── 3D interactive HTML exports ────────────────────────────
# Self-contained but can be large with embedded plotly.js; keep
# locally for exploration, don't bloat the public repo with these.
results/figures/*.html

# ── OS noise ───────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db